hildren:`-- Outgoing traversal\nMATCH (a)-[:KNOWS]->(b) RETURN b\n\n-- Implemented as:\n1. Get node 'a'\n2. getOutgoingEdges(a.id)\n3. Filter edges by type = KNOWS\n4. getConnectedTargetNodes() for each matching edge\n`})}),`\n`,(0,n.jsx)(e.pre,{children:(0,n.jsx)(e.code,{className:\"language-cypher\",children:`-- Incoming traversal\nMATCH (a)<-[:KNOWS]-(b) RETURN b\n\n-- Implemented as:\n1. Get node 'a'\n2. getIncomingEdges(a.id)\n3. Filter edges by type = KNOWS\n4. getConnectedSourceNodes() for each matching edge\n`})}),`\n`,(0,n.jsx)(e.pre,{children:(0,n.jsx)(e.code,{className:\"language-cypher\",children:`-- Bidirectional traversal\nMATCH (a)-[:KNOWS]-(b) RETURN b\n\n-- Implemented as:\n1. Get node 'a'\n2. getAllConnectedEdges(a.id)\n3. Filter edges by type = KNOWS\n4. Extract connected nodes from both directions\n`})}),`\n`,(0,n.jsx)(e.h3,{children:\"Query Execution Flow\"}),`\n`,(0,n.jsx)(t,{chart:`sequenceDiagram\n    participant Q as Cypher Query\n    participant P as Query Planner\n    participant E as Query Executor\n    participant RT as RelationshipTraversal\n    participant DM as DataManager\n\n    Q->>P: MATCH (a)-[:KNOWS]->(b)\n    P->>E: Plan execution\n\n    E->>DM: Get node 'a'\n    DM-->>E: Node object\n\n    E->>RT: getOutgoingEdges(a.id)\n    RT->>DM: Traverse edge list\n    DM-->>RT: Edge objects\n    RT-->>E: Filtered edges\n\n    E->>RT: getConnectedTargetNodes()\n    RT->>DM: Fetch target nodes\n    DM-->>RT: Node objects\n    RT-->>E: Connected nodes\n\n    E-->>Q: Results`}),`\n`,(0,n.jsx)(e.h2,{children:\"Performance Characteristics\"}),`\n`,(0,n.jsx)(e.h3,{children:\"Time Complexity\"}),`\n`,(0,n.jsx)(e.p,{children:`| Operation | Time Complexity | Description |\n|-----------|----------------|-------------|\n| getOutgoingEdges | O(k) | k = number of outgoing edges |\n| getIncomingEdges | O(k) | k = number of incoming edges |\n| getAllConnectedEdges | O(k\\u2081 + k\\u2082) | k\\u2081 = outgoing, k\\u2082 = incoming |\n| getConnectedTargetNodes | O(k) | k = outgoing edges |\n| getConnectedSourceNodes | O(k) | k = incoming edges |\n| getAllConnectedNodes | O(k\\u2081 + k\\u2082) | With deduplication |\n| linkEdge | O(1) | Constant time insertion |\n| unlinkEdge | O(1) | Constant time removal |`}),`\n`,(0,n.jsx)(e.h3,{children:\"Space Complexity\"}),`\n`,(0,n.jsxs)(e.p,{children:[`| Component | Space | Description |\n|-----------|-------|-------------|\n| Node metadata | 2 \\xD7 8 bytes | `,(0,n.jsx)(e.code,{children:\"firstOutEdgeId\"}),\", \",(0,n.jsx)(e.code,{children:\"firstInEdgeId\"}),` |\n| Edge metadata | 4 \\xD7 8 bytes | `,(0,n.jsx)(e.code,{children:\"nextOut\"}),\", \",(0,n.jsx)(e.code,{children:\"prevOut\"}),\", \",(0,n.jsx)(e.code,{children:\"nextIn\"}),\", \",(0,n.jsx)(e.code,{children:\"prevIn\"}),` |\n| Cycle detection | O(k) | `,(0,n.jsx)(e.code,{children:\"std::unordered_set\"}),` during traversal |\n| Result vectors | O(k) | Output edge/node collections |`]}),`\n`,(0,n.jsxs)(e.p,{children:[(0,n.jsx)(e.strong,{children:\"Total Per Edge\"}),\": 32 bytes for traversal pointers (4 \\xD7 int64_t)\"]}),`\n`,(0,n.jsx)(e.h3,{children:\"Memory Overhead\"}),`\n`,(0,n.jsx)(e.pre,{children:(0,n.jsx)(e.code,{children:`For a graph with 1 million edges:\n\nNode Pointers:\n- 2 pointers per node\n- For 100K nodes: 100K \\xD7 2 \\xD7 8 bytes = 1.6 MB\n\nEdge Pointers:\n- 4 pointers per edge\n- 1M \\xD7 4 \\xD7 8 bytes = 32 MB\n\nTotal Traversal Overhead: ~33.6 MB\nPer Edge Average: 33.6 bytes\n`})}),`\n`,(0,n.jsx)(e.h3,{children:\"Performance Characteristics\"}),`\n`,(0,n.jsxs)(e.p,{children:[(0,n.jsx)(e.strong,{children:\"Advantages\"}),\":\"]}),`\n`,(0,n.jsxs)(e.ol,{children:[`\n`,(0,n.jsxs)(e.li,{children:[(0,n.jsx)(e.strong,{children:\"O(1) Edge Operations\"}),\": Insertion and deletion are constant time\"]}),`\n`,(0,n.jsxs)(e.li,{children:[(0,n.jsx)(e.strong,{children:\"No Global Scans\"}),\": Direct access to connected nodes\"]}),`\n`,(0,n.jsxs)(e.li,{children:[(0,n.jsx)(e.strong,{children:\"Cache Friendly\"}),\": Sequential traversal of edge lists\"]}),`\n`,(0,n.jsxs)(e.li,{children:[(0,n.jsx)(e.strong,{children:\"Memory Efficient\"}),\": Only 32 bytes per edge for traversal\"]}),`\n`,(0,n.jsxs)(e.li,{children:[(0,n.jsx)(e.strong,{children:\"Scalable\"}),\": Performance independent of total graph size\"]}),`\n`]}),`\n`,(0,n.jsxs)(e.p,{children:[(0,n.jsx)(e.strong,{children:\"Trade-offs\"}),\":\"]}),`\n`,(0,n.jsxs)(e.ol,{children:[`\n`,(0,n.jsxs)(e.li,{children:[(0,n.jsx)(e.strong,{children:\"Pointer Overhead\"}),\": 32 bytes per edge for traversal pointers\"]}),`\n`,(0,n.jsxs)(e.li,{children:[(0,n.jsx)(e.strong,{children:\"Dereferencing Cost\"}),\": Each edge access requires pointer chase\"]}),`\n`,(0,n.jsxs)(e.li,{children:[(0,n.jsx)(e.strong,{children:\"No Type Indexing\"}),\": Must scan all edges to filter by type\"]}),`\n`,(0,n.jsxs)(e.li,{children:[(0,n.jsx)(e.strong,{children:\"Cycle Detection\"}),\": Adds O(k) space during traversal\"]}),`\n`]}),`\n`,(0,n.jsx)(e.h3,{children:\"Comparison with Alternatives\"}),`\n`,(0,n.jsxs)(e.p,{children:[`| Approach | Edge Access | Memory | Use Case |\n|----------|------------|--------|----------|\n| `,(0,n.jsx)(e.strong,{children:\"Linked List\"}),` (ZYX) | O(k) traversal | 32 bytes/edge | General-purpose graphs |\n| Adjacency Matrix | O(1) lookup | O(V\\xB2) | Dense graphs |\n| Adjacency Array | O(k) scan | O(V + E) | Static graphs |\n| Edge Type Index | O(log n + k) | Additional index | Type-filtered queries |`]}),`\n`,(0,n.jsx)(e.h2,{children:\"Best Practices\"}),`\n`,(0,n.jsxs)(e.ol,{children:[`\n`,(0,n.jsxs)(e.li,{children:[(0,n.jsx)(e.strong,{children:\"Batch Edge Creation\"}),\": Create all nodes first, then link edges to minimize updates\"]}),`\n`,(0,n.jsxs)(e.li,{children:[(0,n.jsx)(e.strong,{children:\"Avoid Cycles\"}),\": Never manually manipulate edge pointers (use \",(0,n.jsx)(e.code,{children:\"linkEdge\"}),\"/\",(0,n.jsx)(e.code,{children:\"unlinkEdge\"}),\")\"]}),`\n`,(0,n.jsxs)(e.li,{children:[(